I"E<p>Liquibase 1.4.0 has been released. Major features include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>IntelliJ Plug-in Support</li>
  <li>Added support for specifying schemas in change log</li>
  <li>MaxDB/SAPDB Support</li>
  <li>Refactored Code</li>
  <li>Can specify data types as <code class="highlighter-rouge">java.sql.Types.*</code></li>
  <li>Support for composite foreign keys</li>
  <li>Improved Maven support</li>
  <li>Bug Fixes</li>
</ul>

<p>Upgrading is simply a matter of replacing the liquibase.jar file. To take advantage of newer change log features, change your XSD declaration to:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;databasechangelog xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/1.4"
    xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    schemalocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/1.4
    http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-1.4.xsd"&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Download Liquibase 1.4 from: <a href="http://www.liquibase.org/download.html">http://www.liquibase.org/download.html</a></p>

:ET